gomodel:SYNGO_5249  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: EM of peroxidase labeling for sigma-1 receptor (SIGMAR1) showed localization at the postsynapse (near but not at the membrane) adjacent to large cholinergic presynaptic terminals.. Experimental description: M&M: \"For preembedding immunoelectron microscopy vibrotome slices 60 um thick of spinal cord from perfused mice were treated with 0.1% NaBH4 for 10 min, washed in PBS and permeabilized with 0.3% saponin.\"\n\n\"Oprs1 mutant (+/-) OprsGt(IRESBetageo)33Lex litters on a C57BL/6J × 129s/SvEv mixed background were purchased from the Mutant Mouse Regional Resource Center, UC Davis, CA.\"\n\nantibody:\nrabbit polyclonal anti sigma-1 (Ramachandran et al., 2007) PMID: 16962337" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
